sub_title: Associate Professor at University of Twente
summary:
Jan Braaksma is an assistant professor Maintenance Engineering in the chair of Maintenance Engineering at the University of Twente and is director of the WCM Summer School. He has worked for the University of Groningen (RuG) and the Dutch Defense Academy (NLDA). He holds a Master’s degree in Business and ICT and a PhD degree in Economics and Business. Jan’s research focuses on on Asset management and Asset life cycle management. 

Specialties: Asset management, Asset life cycle management, RCM/FMEA-based maintenance, investment appraisal, information management, asset information standards
